sudo - command  (super user privilages)    SYNTAX =>  sudo other_command option 
                                                  =>  qsudo, sudoedit â€” execute a command as another user
                                                  =>  for root permission 

sudo mkdir dir_name                 -> for give forcefully permission to make dir
sudo apt-get install package_name   -> for give permission to install pakages
sudo -s                             -> for reach superuser mode
sudo -i                             -> for home dir
sudo passwd user-name               -> for add passard or change the passward
sudo useradd user_name -m -s /usr/bin/bash -g users -c "comment"  -> for add user
sudo userdel user_name              -> for remove the user but it can't be remove user from home  
sudo userdel -r user-name           -> for remove user completely 
sudo groupadd group_name            -> for add group (group add in system datewise)
